## 📍 Phase 4: Fence Pointers

### Configurable Parameters

- Block size: 4KB, 8KB, 16KB
- Number of fence pointers per SSTable

### Implementation Plan

- Divide SSTable into blocks.
- Store (key_min, byte_offset) for each block.
- On `get(key)`, binary search fence pointers then read block.

### 🔧 Hyperparameter Tuning for Fence Pointers (Phase 4)

#### Tunable Parameters

| Parameter            | Description                                        | Candidate Values |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- | ---------------- |
| `block_size`         | Size of each on-disk block (affects granularity)   | 4KB, 8KB, 16KB   |
| `pointers_per_table` | Number of fence pointers (derived from block size) | implicit         |

#### Test Design

- Load 1M key-value pairs into SSTables with Bloom filters enabled
- Run 100k `get()` queries for random keys
- Compare:
  - No fence pointers
  - Fence pointers only
  - Fence pointers + Bloom filters

#### Metrics Collected

- Fence pointer seek time
- Block I/O (bytes per lookup)
- Average `get()` latency

#### Visualizations

- 📈 Line chart: `Get latency` vs. `block size`
- 📊 Bar chart: `Avg. blocks accessed per query` by block size
- 📈 Line chart: `Latency` (None vs. Fence vs. Fence+Bloom)

#### Goal

Find the best `block_size` that:

- Minimizes I/O while keeping pointer overhead low
- Offers measurable improvement in seek time
- Pairs well with Bloom filters (combined effectiveness)

